Title: We Are All Nerds: The Literary Works of Neal Stephenson
Description:
If you and I ever had a longer conversation, chances are that Neal Stephenson might have come up once or twice.
As contemporary authors go, Neal’s books are by far the most enthralling
on my long and ever-growing reading list. This post is primarily written
for people that usually shy away from reading what they consider
‘science fiction’ literature because they consider it to be
insufficiently serious or just plain weird.1 I hope to dispel some
myths and whet your appetite for this type of books.

Title: Stringing together several free tiers to host an application with zero cost using fly.io, Litestream and Cloudflare
Description:
The image was generated by putting the blog post title into DALL-E 2. Quite fitting!
I have a side project called bostadsbussen. It scrapes property listings for the Swedish real estate market. The site needs to persist data in the form of user accounts, property data and images.
At the time of writing this post I am currently on a sabbatical. With my income at 0, I want to keep the cost of hosting my side project as low as possible.

Title: On Caching Elixir Beam files · Anantha Kumaran
Description:
Nowadays it’s a standard practice to cache dependencies and compiled
artifacts to improve CI build time. For Elixir apps, this
would mean caching the contents of _build and deps. The compiler
is smart enough to figure out what needs to be recompiled. This setup
was working well except for one annoying issue.
